{"key":"processedPost-7009354","value":{"id":7009354,"first":7008562,"last":7010894,"when":1181006430,"utime":"06/05/07 04:20 AM","content":"The color of the light they get is not relevant to the color of the tub they're in.  By 'blue' light, we mean light at the high end of the color temperature spectrum, measured in Kelvin.  You'll want to cut a square in the top of that tub and glue a piece of clear Plexiglas or lay a sheet of window glass over it. Best would be to use a piece of clear Plexiglas over the entire top to replace the pink lid. Use a fluorescent lamp, or place the tub near a window for natural lighting.<br />RR","title":"Re: My pink fc - a question about light.","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}